Net assessment: CD 1 preserves the midrange guitar weight, analogue warmth, low‑compression dynamic punch and stacked harmonies that align with my core priorities. CD 2, while competent and vocal‑forward with controlled compression, sacrifices the analogue warmth and rhythmic punch I specifically value, so I choose CD 1.

